text: Bishkurayevo () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Bishkurayevsky Selsoviet, Tuymazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 680 as of 2010. There are 7 streets. == Geography == It is located 45 km from Tuymazy. == References == Category:Rural localities in Tuymazinsky District
title: Bishkurayevo, Tuymazinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
